<subSubSection id="B5E06557FFB7BA6C6CAA05D7FE382936" pageId="4" pageNumber="140" type="description">
<paragraph id="FD4536DCFFB7BA6C6CAA05D7FD632BF2" blockId="4.[151,1436,258,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis id="CF8EEACEFFB7BA6C6CAA05D7FEC02BAA" bold="true" box="[199,381,402,427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Measurements.</emphasis>
Head length (1.4); head width (2.5); pronotal length (2.5); pronotal width (6.2); width of scutellum at base (5.2); scutellar width (4.0); length of antennal segments (I: 0.7; II: 1.0; III: 1.0; IV and V missing); total length (11.9); abdominal width (7.6).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD4536DCFFB7BA6C6CAA05BBFDA128CA" blockId="4.[151,1436,258,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis id="CF8EEACEFFB7BA6C6CAA05BBFE862816" bold="true" box="[199,315,510,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Diagnose.</emphasis>
Pronotum smooth. Corium with light brown punctures. Metasternal process (
<figureCitation id="65C12A59FFB7BA6C68F205BBFB402816" box="[1183,1277,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1981,2003]" captionTargetBox="[211,1370,295,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1385,195,1951]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A – D. Edessa exigusternata sp. n.: A – C, pygophore in dorsal, ventral and posterior view, respectively; D, metasternal process. Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/545754/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2 D</figureCitation>
) with anterior bifurcation strongly reduced, almost vestigial. Peritreme just surpassing half of the distance between ostiole of the scent gland and lateral margin of the body (
<figureCitation id="65C12A59FFB7BA6C6ECB0603FCB3285E" box="[678,782,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[212,1372,254,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[200,1387,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. A – E. Peritreme: A, Edessa viridula sp. n.; B, Edessa exigusternata sp. n.; C, Edessa angusticlada sp. n.; D, Edessa rugulata sp. n.; E, Edessa eucnema sp. n.. Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/545760/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 8 B</figureCitation>
). Evaporatorium with a long and barely raised crest in mesopleuron, actually the bordering sulci emphasize the crest; contiguous margin of meso and metapleuron not raised; metapleuron even without any crest. Spiracles black (
<figureCitation id="65C12A59FFB7BA6C6F5106CBFC2A28A6" box="[828,919,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1981,2003]" captionTargetBox="[211,1370,295,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1385,195,1951]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A – D. Edessa exigusternata sp. n.: A – C, pygophore in dorsal, ventral and posterior view, respectively; D, metasternal process. Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/545754/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2 B</figureCitation>
) and trichobothria not placed in a light yellow callus. Antennae and legs spotless.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD4536DCFFB7BA6C6CAA0693FE382936" blockId="4.[151,1436,258,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis id="CF8EEACEFFB7BA6C6CAA0693FEB928EE" bold="true" box="[199,260,726,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="65C12A59FFB7BA6C6D790693FE2628EE" box="[276,411,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1981,2003]" captionTargetBox="[211,1370,295,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1385,195,1951]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A – D. Edessa exigusternata sp. n.: A – C, pygophore in dorsal, ventral and posterior view, respectively; D, metasternal process. Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/545754/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Figs 2 A–C</figureCitation>
). Superior process of the genital cup reduced to a black line. Ventral part of the paramere with a short globose and a digitiform long lobes, base wider than distal part; digitiform and dorsal lobes distinctly projected posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B5E06557FFB7BA6C6CAA0707FEDC29A3" pageId="4" pageNumber="140" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FD4536DCFFB7BA6C6CAA0707FEDC29A3" blockId="4.[151,1436,258,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis id="CF8EEACEFFB7BA6C6CAA0707FEF2295A" bold="true" box="[199,335,834,859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Comments.</emphasis>
Female unknown. 
<taxonomicName id="3AFA4D5FFFB7BA6C6E480706FCA9295B" box="[549,788,835,859]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exigusternata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="CF8EEACEFFB7BA6C6E480706FCA9295B" box="[549,788,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Edessa exigusternata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D4BD57B5FFB7BA6C6F760707FCE7295A" box="[795,858,834,859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140" rank="species">
<emphasis id="CF8EEACEFFB7BA6C6F760707FCE7295A" bold="true" box="[795,858,834,859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the most peculiar of the five species with several differences from the other species and was included in this group due to shape of the paramere and superior process of the genital cup.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
